414
00:29:31,249 --> 00:29:37,019
What was the relation between them, andwhat the object of his repeated visits?

415
00:29:37,019 --> 00:29:42,379
Was she his client, his friend, or hismistress?

416
00:29:42,379 --> 00:29:47,249
If the former, she had probably transferredthe photograph to his keeping.

417
00:29:47,249 --> 00:29:50,044
If the latter, it was less likely.

418
00:29:50,044 --> 00:29:55,007
On the issue of this question dependedwhether I should continue my work at Briony

419
00:29:55,007 --> 00:29:59,082
Lodge, or turn my attention to thegentleman's chambers in the Temple.

420
00:29:59,082 --> 00:30:04,059
It was a delicate point, and it widened thefield of my inquiry.

421
00:30:04,059 --> 00:30:09,359
I fear that I bore you with these details,but I have to let you see my little

422
00:30:09,359 --> 00:30:13,082
difficulties, if you are to understand thesituation."

423
00:30:13,082 --> 00:30:18,749
"I am following you closely," I answered.

424
00:30:18,749 --> 00:30:24,239
"I was still balancing the matter in mymind when a hansom cab drove up to Briony

425
00:30:24,239 --> 00:30:26,081
Lodge, and a gentleman sprang out.

426
00:30:26,081 --> 00:30:33,031
He was a remarkably handsome man, dark,aquiline, and moustached--evidently the man

427
00:30:33,031 --> 00:30:35,159
of whom I had heard.

428
00:30:35,159 --> 00:30:40,081
He appeared to be in a great hurry, shoutedto the cabman to wait, and brushed past the

429
00:30:40,081 --> 00:30:45,479
maid who opened the door with the air of aman who was thoroughly at home.

430
00:30:45,479 --> 00:30:49,085
"He was in the house about half an hour,and I could catch glimpses of him in the

431
00:30:49,085 --> 00:30:55,057
windows of the sitting-room, pacing up anddown, talking excitedly, and waving his

432
00:30:55,057 --> 00:30:56,081
arms.

433
00:30:56,081 --> 00:31:01,072
Of her I could see nothing.Presently he emerged, looking even more

434
00:31:01,072 --> 00:31:03,859
flurried than before.

435
00:31:03,859 --> 00:31:08,489
As he stepped up to the cab, he pulled agold watch from his pocket and looked at it

436
00:31:08,489 --> 00:31:14,529
earnestly, 'Drive like the devil,' heshouted, 'first to Gross & Hankey's in

437
00:31:14,529 --> 00:31:19,409
