444
00:31:44,529 --> 00:31:48,869
I only caught a glimpse of her at themoment, but she was a lovely woman, with a

445
00:31:48,869 --> 00:31:51,849
face that a man might die for.

446
00:31:51,849 --> 00:31:56,759
"'The Church of St. Monica, John,' shecried, 'and half a sovereign if you reach

447
00:31:56,759 --> 00:32:01,081
it in twenty minutes.'"This was quite too good to lose, Watson.

448
00:32:01,081 --> 00:32:06,083
I was just balancing whether I should runfor it, or whether I should perch behind

449
00:32:06,083 --> 00:32:10,031
her landau when a cab came through thestreet.

450
00:32:10,031 --> 00:32:14,369
The driver looked twice at such a shabbyfare, but I jumped in before he could

451
00:32:14,369 --> 00:32:14,081
object.

452
00:32:14,081 --> 00:32:20,057
'The Church of St. Monica,' said I, 'andhalf a sovereign if you reach it in twenty

453
00:32:20,057 --> 00:32:21,056
minutes.'

454
00:32:21,056 --> 00:32:25,629
It was twenty-five minutes to twelve, andof course it was clear enough what was in

455
00:32:25,629 --> 00:32:29,139
the wind."My cabby drove fast.

456
00:32:29,139 --> 00:32:34,069
I don't think I ever drove faster, but theothers were there before us.

457
