The cab and the landau with their steaminghorses were in front of the door when I

458
00:32:38,369 --> 00:32:38,999
arrived.

459
00:32:38,999 --> 00:32:45,018
I paid the man and hurried into the church.There was not a soul there save the two

460
00:32:45,018 --> 00:32:50,229
whom I had followed and a surplicedclergyman, who seemed to be expostulating

461
00:32:50,229 --> 00:32:51,045
with them.

462
00:32:51,045 --> 00:32:55,029
They were all three standing in a knot infront of the altar.

463
00:32:55,029 --> 00:33:00,046
I lounged up the side aisle like any otheridler who has dropped into a church.

464
00:33:00,046 --> 00:33:06,369
Suddenly, to my surprise, the three at thealtar faced round to me, and Godfrey Norton

465
00:33:06,369 --> 00:33:09,045
came running as hard as he could towardsme.

466
00:33:09,045 --> 00:33:11,045
"'Thank God,' he cried.

467
00:33:11,045 --> 00:33:12,889
'You'll do.Come!

468
00:33:12,889 --> 00:33:15,619
Come!'"'What then?'

469
00:33:15,619 --> 00:33:17,034
I asked.

470
00:33:17,034 --> 00:33:21,769
"'Come, man, come, only three minutes, orit won't be legal.'

471
00:33:21,769 --> 00:33:27,031
"I was half-dragged up to the altar, andbefore I knew where I was I found myself

472
00:33:27,031 --> 00:33:32,379
mumbling responses which were whispered inmy ear, and vouching for things of which I

473
00:33:32,379 --> 00:33:35,008
knew nothing, and generally assisting in

474
00:33:35,008 --> 00:33:41,093
the secure tying up of Irene Adler,spinster, to Godfrey Norton, bachelor.

475
00:33:41,093 --> 00:33:46,047
It was all done in an instant, and therewas the gentleman thanking me on the one

476
00:33:46,047 --> 00:33:52,409
side and the lady on the other, while theclergyman beamed on me in front.

477
00:33:52,409 --> 00:33:58,279
It was the most preposterous position inwhich I ever found myself in my life, and

478
00:33:58,279 --> 00:34:02,095
it was the thought of it that started melaughing just now.

479
00:34:02,095 --> 00:34:07,259
It seems that there had been someinformality about their license, that the

480
00:34:07,259 --> 00:34:12,054
clergyman absolutely refused to marry themwithout a witness of some sort, and that my

481
00:34:12,054 --> 00:34:14,719
lucky appearance saved the bridegroom from

482
00:34:14,719 --> 00:34:19,159
having to sally out into the streets insearch of a best man.

483
00:34:19,159 --> 00:34:23,989
The bride gave me a sovereign, and I meanto wear it on my watch-chain in memory of

484
00:34:23,989 --> 00:34:25,037
the occasion."

485
00:34:25,037 --> 00:34:31,929
"This is a very unexpected turn ofaffairs," said I; "and what then?"

486
00:34:31,929 --> 00:34:35,729
"Well, I found my plans very seriouslymenaced.

487
00:34:35,729 --> 00:34:40,479
It looked as if the pair might take animmediate departure, and so necessitate

488
00:34:40,479 --> 00:34:43,479
very prompt and energetic measures on mypart.

489
00:34:43,479 --> 00:34:49,499
At the church door, however, theyseparated, he driving back to the Temple,

490
00:34:49,499 --> 00:34:55,219
and she to her own house.'I shall drive out in the park at five as

491
00:34:55,219 --> 00:34:57,033
usual,' she said as she left him.

492
00:34:57,033 --> 00:35:01,048
I heard no more.They drove away in different directions,

493
00:35:01,048 --> 00:35:04,051
and I went off to make my ownarrangements."

494
00:35:04,051 --> 00:35:06,209
"Which are?"

495
00:35:06,209 --> 00:35:11,439
"Some cold beef and a glass of beer," heanswered, ringing the bell.

496
00:35:11,439 --> 00:35:16,009
"I have been too busy to think of food, andI am likely to be busier still this

497
00:35:16,009 --> 00:35:17,012
evening.

498
00:35:17,012 --> 00:35:21,052
By the way, Doctor, I shall want your co-operation."

499
00:35:21,052 --> 00:35:26,088
"I shall be delighted.""You don't mind breaking the law?"

500
00:35:26,088 --> 00:35:28,088
"Not in the least."

501
00:35:28,088 --> 00:35:34,011
"Nor running a chance of arrest?""Not in a good cause."

502
00:35:34,011 --> 00:35:39,037
"Oh, the cause is excellent!""Then I am your man."

503
00:35:39,037 --> 00:35:42,059
"I was sure that I might rely on you."

504
00:35:42,059 --> 00:35:47,949
"But what is it you wish?""When Mrs. Turner has brought in the tray I

505
00:35:47,949 --> 00:35:49,098
will make it clear to you.

506
00:35:49,098 --> 00:35:56,006
Now," he said as he turned hungrily on thesimple fare that our landlady had provided,

507
00:35:56,006 --> 00:35:59,037
"I must discuss it while I eat, for I havenot much time.

508
00:35:59,037 --> 00:36:01,055
It is nearly five now.

509
00:36:01,055 --> 00:36:06,159
In two hours we must be on the scene ofaction.

510
00:36:06,159 --> 00:36:11,031
Miss Irene, or Madame, rather, returns fromher drive at seven.

511
00:36:11,031 --> 00:36:14,057
We must be at Briony Lodge to meet her."

512
00:36:14,057 --> 00:36:18,659
"And what then?""You must leave that to me.

513
00:36:18,659 --> 00:36:23,086
I have already arranged what is to occur.There is only one point on which I must

514
00:36:23,086 --> 00:36:24,077
insist.

515
00:36:24,077 --> 00:36:29,084
You must not interfere, come what may.You understand?"

516
00:36:29,084 --> 00:36:34,469
"I am to be neutral?""To do nothing whatever.

517
00:36:34,469 --> 00:36:38,459
There will probably be some smallunpleasantness.

518
00:36:38,459 --> 00:36:42,037
Do not join in it.It will end in my being conveyed into the

519
00:36:42,037 --> 00:36:43,005
house.

520
00:36:43,005 --> 00:36:47,008
Four or five minutes afterwards thesitting-room window will open.

521
00:36:47,008 --> 00:36:51,006
You are to station yourself close to thatopen window."

522
00:36:51,006 --> 00:36:53,002
"Yes."

523
00:36:53,002 --> 00:36:56,659
"You are to watch me, for I will be visibleto you."

524
00:36:56,659 --> 00:36:58,007
"Yes."

525
00:36:58,007 --> 00:37:03,179
"And when I raise my hand--so--you willthrow into the room what I give you to

526
00:37:03,179 --> 00:37:08,037
throw, and will, at the same time, raisethe cry of fire.

527
00:37:08,037 --> 00:37:09,037
You quite follow me?"

528
00:37:09,037 --> 00:37:15,179
"Entirely.""It is nothing very formidable," he said,

529
00:37:15,179 --> 00:37:18,083
taking a long cigar-shaped roll from hispocket.

530
00:37:18,083 --> 00:37:23,081
"It is an ordinary plumber's smoke-rocket,fitted with a cap at either end to make it

531
00:37:23,081 --> 00:37:28,007
self-lighting.Your task is confined to that.

532
00:37:28,007 --> 00:37:33,024
When you raise your cry of fire, it will betaken up by quite a number of people.

533
00:37:33,024 --> 00:37:38,008
You may then walk to the end of the street,and I will rejoin you in ten minutes.

534
00:37:38,008 --> 00:37:39,098
I hope that I have made myself clear?"

535
00:37:39,098 --> 00:37:47,929
"I am to remain neutral, to get near thewindow, to watch you, and at the signal to

536
00:37:47,929 --> 00:37:54,179
throw in this object, then to raise the cryof fire, and to wait you at the corner of

537
00:37:54,179 --> 00:37:55,049
the street."

538
00:37:55,049 --> 00:38:00,049
"Precisely.""Then you may entirely rely on me."

539
00:38:00,049 --> 00:38:04,053
"That is excellent.I think, perhaps, it is almost time that I

540
00:38:04,053 --> 00:38:08,076
prepare for the new role I have to play."

541
00:38:08,076 --> 00:38:13,002
He disappeared into his bedroom andreturned in a few minutes in the character

542
00:38:13,002 --> 00:38:18,003
of an amiable and simple-mindedNonconformist clergyman.

543
00:38:18,003 --> 00:38:25,011
His broad black hat, his baggy trousers,his white tie, his sympathetic smile, and

544
00:38:25,011 --> 00:38:30,085
general look of peering and benevolentcuriosity were such as Mr. John Hare alone

545
00:38:30,085 --> 00:38:32,036
could have equalled.

546
00:38:32,036 --> 00:38:35,949
It was not merely that Holmes changed hiscostume.

547
00:38:35,949 --> 00:38:41,051
His expression, his manner, his very soulseemed to vary with every fresh part that

548
00:38:41,051 --> 00:38:42,098
he assumed.

549
00:38:42,098 --> 00:38:48,037
The stage lost a fine actor, even asscience lost an acute reasoner, when he

550
00:38:48,037 --> 00:38:50,035
became a specialist in crime.

551
00:38:50,035 --> 00:38:57,015
It was a quarter past six when we leftBaker Street, and it still wanted ten

552
00:38:57,015 --> 00:39:00,031
minutes to the hour when we found ourselvesin Serpentine Avenue.

553
00:39:00,031 --> 00:39:06,014
It was already dusk, and the lamps werejust being lighted as we paced up and down

554
00:39:06,014 --> 00:39:11,012
in front of Briony Lodge, waiting for thecoming of its occupant.

555
00:39:11,012 --> 00:39:15,081
The house was just such as I had picturedit from Sherlock Holmes' succinct

556
00:39:15,081 --> 00:39:21,004
description, but the locality appeared tobe less private than I expected.

557
00:39:21,004 --> 00:39:26,669
On the contrary, for a small street in aquiet neighbourhood, it was remarkably

558
00:39:26,669 --> 00:39:28,005
animated.

559
00:39:28,005 --> 00:39:32,078
There was a group of shabbily dressed mensmoking and laughing in a corner, a

560
00:39:32,078 --> 00:39:37,029
scissors-grinder with his wheel, twoguardsmen who were flirting with a nurse-

561
00:39:37,029 --> 00:39:40,012
girl, and several well-dressed young men

562
00:39:40,012 --> 00:39:44,003
who were lounging up and down with cigarsin their mouths.

563
00:39:44,003 --> 00:39:49,082
"You see," remarked Holmes, as we paced toand fro in front of the house, "this

564
00:39:49,082 --> 00:39:54,009
marriage rather simplifies matters.The photograph becomes a double-edged

565
00:39:54,009 --> 00:39:56,055
weapon now.

566
00:39:56,055 --> 00:40:02,054
The chances are that she would be as averseto its being seen by Mr. Godfrey Norton, as

567
00:40:02,054 --> 00:40:06,449
our client is to its coming to the eyes ofhis princess.

568
00:40:06,449 --> 00:40:10,006
Now the question is, Where are we to findthe photograph?"

569
00:40:10,006 --> 00:40:16,028
"Where, indeed?""It is most unlikely that she carries it

570
00:40:16,028 --> 00:40:17,399
about with her.

571
00:40:17,399 --> 00:40:22,029
It is cabinet size.Too large for easy concealment about a

572
00:40:22,029 --> 00:40:25,969
woman's dress.She knows that the King is capable of

573
00:40:25,969 --> 00:40:28,035
having her waylaid and searched.

574
00:40:28,035 --> 00:40:31,085
Two attempts of the sort have already beenmade.

575
00:40:31,085 --> 00:40:36,008
We may take it, then, that she does notcarry it about with her."

576
00:40:36,008 --> 00:40:38,001
"Where, then?"

577
00:40:38,001 --> 00:40:43,033
"Her banker or her lawyer.There is that double possibility.

578
00:40:43,033 --> 00:40:49,008
But I am inclined to think neither.Women are naturally secretive, and they

579
00:40:49,008 --> 00:40:51,719
like to do their own secreting.

580
00:40:51,719 --> 00:40:57,003
Why should she hand it over to anyone else?She could trust her own guardianship, but

581
00:40:57,003 --> 00:41:01,074
she could not tell what indirect orpolitical influence might be brought to

582
00:41:01,074 --> 00:41:03,085
bear upon a business man.

583
00:41:03,085 --> 00:41:09,036
Besides, remember that she had resolved touse it within a few days.

584
00:41:09,036 --> 00:41:12,449
It must be where she can lay her hands uponit.

585
00:41:12,449 --> 00:41:15,024
It must be in her own house."

586
00:41:15,024 --> 00:41:19,014
"But it has twice been burgled.""Pshaw!

587
00:41:19,014 --> 00:41:24,098
They did not know how to look.""But how will you look?"

588
00:41:24,098 --> 00:41:26,099
"I will not look."

589
00:41:26,099 --> 00:41:30,037
"What then?""I will get her to show me."

590
00:41:30,037 --> 00:41:37,006
"But she will refuse.""She will not be able to.

591
00:41:37,006 --> 00:41:39,049
But I hear the rumble of wheels.

592
00:41:39,049 --> 00:41:45,459
It is her carriage.Now carry out my orders to the letter."

593
00:41:45,459 --> 00:41:49,084
As he spoke the gleam of the side-lights ofa carriage came round the curve of the

594
00:41:49,084 --> 00:41:51,179
avenue.

595
00:41:51,179 --> 00:41:56,049
It was a smart little landau which rattledup to the door of Briony Lodge.

596
00:41:56,049 --> 00:42:01,033
As it pulled up, one of the loafing men atthe corner dashed forward to open the door

597
00:42:01,033 --> 00:42:06,005
in the hope of earning a copper, but waselbowed away by another loafer, who had

598
00:42:06,005 --> 00:42:08,035
rushed up with the same intention.

599
00:42:08,035 --> 00:42:12,919
A fierce quarrel broke out, which wasincreased by the two guardsmen, who took

600
00:42:12,919 --> 00:42:18,649
sides with one of the loungers, and by thescissors-grinder, who was equally hot upon

601
00:42:18,649 --> 00:42:20,209
the other side.

602
00:42:20,209 --> 00:42:25,057
A blow was struck, and in an instant thelady, who had stepped from her carriage,

603
00:42:25,057 --> 00:42:31,002
was the centre of a little knot of flushedand struggling men, who struck savagely at

604
00:42:31,002 --> 00:42:34,149
each other with their fists and sticks.

605
00:42:34,149 --> 00:42:39,719
Holmes dashed into the crowd to protect thelady; but just as he reached her he gave a

606
00:42:39,719 --> 00:42:44,057
cry and dropped to the ground, with theblood running freely down his face.

607
00:42:44,057 --> 00:42:49,409
At his fall the guardsmen took to theirheels in one direction and the loungers in

608
00:42:49,409 --> 00:42:53,088
the other, while a number of better-dressedpeople, who had watched the scuffle without

609
00:42:53,088 --> 00:43:00,049
taking part in it, crowded in to help thelady and to attend to the injured man.

610
00:43:00,049 --> 00:43:06,699
Irene Adler, as I will still call her, hadhurried up the steps; but she stood at the

611
00:43:06,699 --> 00:43:12,024
top with her superb figure outlined againstthe lights of the hall, looking back into

612
00:43:12,024 --> 00:43:14,028
the street.

613
00:43:14,028 --> 00:43:18,012
"Is the poor gentleman much hurt?" sheasked.

614
00:43:18,012 --> 00:43:24,074
"He is dead," cried several voices."No, no, there's life in him!" shouted

615
00:43:24,074 --> 00:43:25,084
another.

616
00:43:25,084 --> 00:43:28,061
"But he'll be gone before you can get himto hospital."

617
00:43:28,061 --> 00:43:34,076
"He's a brave fellow," said a woman."They would have had the lady's purse and

618
00:43:34,076 --> 00:43:37,024
watch if it hadn't been for him.

619
00:43:37,024 --> 00:43:43,429
They were a gang, and a rough one, too.Ah, he's breathing now."

620
00:43:43,429 --> 00:43:47,073
"He can't lie in the street.May we bring him in, marm?"

621
00:43:47,073 --> 00:43:49,209
"Surely.

622
00:43:49,209 --> 00:43:53,013
Bring him into the sitting-room.There is a comfortable sofa.

623
00:43:53,013 --> 00:43:53,659
This way, please!"

624
00:43:53,659 --> 00:44:00,032
Slowly and solemnly he was borne intoBriony Lodge and laid out in the principal

625
00:44:00,032 --> 00:44:05,051
room, while I still observed theproceedings from my post by the window.

626
00:44:05,051 --> 00:44:10,054
The lamps had been lit, but the blinds hadnot been drawn, so that I could see Holmes

627
00:44:10,054 --> 00:44:11,076
as he lay upon the couch.

628
00:44:11,076 --> 00:44:17,000
I do not know whether he was seized withcompunction at that moment for the part he

629
00:44:17,000 --> 00:44:22,076
was playing, but I know that I never feltmore heartily ashamed of myself in my life

630
00:44:22,076 --> 00:44:24,082
than when I saw the beautiful creature

631
00:44:24,082 --> 00:44:30,079
against whom I was conspiring, or the graceand kindliness with which she waited upon

632
00:44:30,079 --> 00:44:32,083
the injured man.

633
00:44:32,083 --> 00:44:37,084
And yet it would be the blackest treacheryto Holmes to draw back now from the part

634
00:44:37,084 --> 00:44:42,063
which he had intrusted to me.I hardened my heart, and took the smoke-

635
00:44:42,063 --> 00:44:45,159
rocket from under my ulster.

636
00:44:45,159 --> 00:44:48,649
After all, I thought, we are not injuringher.

637
00:44:48,649 --> 00:44:52,087
We are but preventing her from injuringanother.

638
00:44:52,087 --> 00:44:57,049
Holmes had sat up upon the couch, and I sawhim motion like a man who is in need of

639
00:44:57,049 --> 00:45:01,009
air.A maid rushed across and threw open the

640
00:45:01,009 --> 00:45:01,064
window.

641
00:45:01,064 --> 00:45:06,899
At the same instant I saw him raise hishand and at the signal I tossed my rocket

642
00:45:06,899 --> 00:45:10,008
into the room with a cry of "Fire!"

643
00:45:10,008 --> 00:45:15,037
The word was no sooner out of my mouth thanthe whole crowd of spectators, well dressed

644
00:45:15,037 --> 00:45:21,054
and ill--gentlemen, ostlers, and servant-maids--joined in a general shriek of

645
00:45:21,054 --> 00:45:23,024
"Fire!"

646
00:45:23,024 --> 00:45:27,083
Thick clouds of smoke curled through theroom and out at the open window.

647
00:45:27,083 --> 00:45:32,031
I caught a glimpse of rushing figures, anda moment later the voice of Holmes from

648
00:45:32,031 --> 00:45:36,959
within assuring them that it was a falsealarm.

649
00:45:36,959 --> 00:45:41,089
Slipping through the shouting crowd I mademy way to the corner of the street, and in

650
00:45:41,089 --> 00:45:47,005
ten minutes was rejoiced to find myfriend's arm in mine, and to get away from

651
00:45:47,005 --> 00:45:48,086
the scene of uproar.

652
00:45:48,086 --> 00:45:53,449
He walked swiftly and in silence for somefew minutes until we had turned down one of

653
00:45:53,449 --> 00:45:58,007
the quiet streets which lead towards theEdgeware Road.

654
00:45:58,007 --> 00:46:01,079
"You did it very nicely, Doctor," heremarked.

655
00:46:01,079 --> 00:46:05,959
"Nothing could have been better.It is all right."

656
00:46:05,959 --> 00:46:08,004
"You have the photograph?"

657
00:46:08,004 --> 00:46:13,005
"I know where it is.""And how did you find out?"

658
00:46:13,005 --> 00:46:18,079
"She showed me, as I told you she would.""I am still in the dark."

659
00:46:18,079 --> 00:46:23,949
"I do not wish to make a mystery," said he,laughing.

660
00:46:23,949 --> 00:46:28,089
"The matter was perfectly simple.You, of course, saw that everyone in the

661
00:46:28,089 --> 00:46:30,057
street was an accomplice.

662
00:46:30,057 --> 00:46:34,026
They were all engaged for the evening.""I guessed as much."

663
00:46:34,026 --> 00:46:39,005
"Then, when the row broke out, I had alittle moist red paint in the palm of my

664
00:46:39,005 --> 00:46:40,179
hand.

665
00:46:40,179 --> 00:46:45,052
I rushed forward, fell down, clapped myhand to my face, and became a piteous

666
00:46:45,052 --> 00:46:47,939
spectacle.It is an old trick."

667
00:46:47,939 --> 00:46:51,099
"That also I could fathom."

668
00:46:51,099 --> 00:46:55,074
"Then they carried me in.She was bound to have me in.

669
00:46:55,074 --> 00:47:00,000
What else could she do?And into her sitting-room, which was the

670
00:47:00,000 --> 00:47:02,054
very room which I suspected.

671
00:47:02,054 --> 00:47:06,026
It lay between that and her bedroom, and Iwas determined to see which.

672
00:47:06,026 --> 00:47:12,057
They laid me on a couch, I motioned forair, they were compelled to open the

673
00:47:12,057 --> 00:47:15,062
window, and you had your chance."

674
00:47:15,062 --> 00:47:19,149
"How did that help you?""It was all-important.

675
00:47:19,149 --> 00:47:25,012
When a woman thinks that her house is onfire, her instinct is at once to rush to

676
00:47:25,012 --> 00:47:27,076
the thing which she values most.

677
00:47:27,076 --> 00:47:32,719
It is a perfectly overpowering impulse, andI have more than once taken advantage of

678
00:47:32,719 --> 00:47:33,074
it.

679
00:47:33,074 --> 00:47:39,000
In the case of the Darlington substitutionscandal it was of use to me, and also in

680
00:47:39,000 --> 00:47:43,699
the Arnsworth Castle business.A married woman grabs at her baby; an

681
00:47:43,699 --> 00:47:46,024
unmarried one reaches for her jewel-box.

682
00:47:46,024 --> 00:47:52,006
Now it was clear to me that our lady of to-day had nothing in the house more precious

683
00:47:52,006 --> 00:47:57,083
to her than what we are in quest of.She would rush to secure it.

684
00:47:57,083 --> 00:48:00,073
The alarm of fire was admirably done.

685
00:48:00,073 --> 00:48:04,051
